// // This module implements an EEPROM cell that stores a single bit of data. It has inputs for data (`d`), write enable (`we`), and clock (`clk`). When `we` is high, the value of `d` is stored in the cell on the falling edge of the clock. The output (`q`) reflects the stored value, and it remains unchanged when `we` is low.
module eeprom_cell (
    input wire clk,
    input wire we,
    input wire d,
    output reg q
);
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (we) begin
            q <= d;
        end
    end
endmodule
